  "notes": "Proto-Boro-Garo (~2000–1500 BCE). Reconstructed ancestor of Bodo, Garo, Dimasa, Kokborok, Tiwa, Rabha. Sino-Tibetan > Tibeto-Burman > Sal branch. Aspirated/plain stop contrast; incipient tone; prefixing morphology; SVO order (atypical for TB). Refs: Matisoff (2003), Burling (2003), Benedict (1972).",
